Transcription.Text: David, Who sensed the various opinions and felt some pressure might eventually be brought to bear on Caroline to think again, pleaded for an early marriage. She was not adverse to the suggestion, but he had to use a deal of pressure before she would agree to a quick marriage at a registry in Starminster.
